# deploy.env.example -- copy to deploy.env, fill it in, then run ./deploy.sh
#
#   cp deploy.env.example deploy.env    # then edit deploy.env
#
# deploy.env holds YOUR keys and is gitignored. NEVER commit the real deploy.env.
# Every value is for YOUR OWN Cloudflare + RunPod accounts; you pay your own bills.
# Where to get each value is in docs/DEPLOYMENT.md sections 2a-2d.

# ---- Which parts to install --------------------------------------------------
# standard   = studio core + cloud/own-GPU render + the media stack (5 always-on CPU containers on
#              YOUR box, reached over Workers VPC). deploy.sh creates the tunnel + VPC services for
#              you; you just run `docker compose -f containers/compose.yaml up -d` afterwards.
# satellites = also the 3 opt-in GPU finish modules (upscale / lip-sync / speech-upscale), each on
#              its own separate RunPod endpoint (see the SATELLITES section below).
# Start with standard. (values: standard | satellites)
VIVIJURE_PROFILE=standard

# ---- Where your studio lives -------------------------------------------------
# The web address your studio answers on. You must own this name in Cloudflare (a zone in your
# account).
# No domain? Use your workers.dev address instead: vivijure-studio.<your-subdomain>.workers.dev
# (find <your-subdomain> at dash.cloudflare.com -> Workers & Pages -> your subdomain). deploy.sh
# detects *.workers.dev and serves there directly; no DNS or custom domain needed.
DEPLOY_HOSTNAME=studio.example.com

# ---- How you log in (docs/SECURITY.md) ----------------------------------------
# token  = built-in login (the default). deploy.sh mints a strong random token, stores it as a
#          worker secret, and prints it ONCE at the end -- save it; the studio asks for it on
#          first load. No Cloudflare Zero Trust setup needed.
# access = Cloudflare Access in front of the studio (recommended for teams/orgs). Requires the
#          two ACCESS_* values below. (values: token | access)
AUTH_MODE=token

# ---- Cloudflare (docs/DEPLOYMENT.md 2a) --------------------------------------
# Account id: dash.cloudflare.com -> right sidebar "Account ID". An id, not a secret.
CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=
# API token: dash -> My Profile -> API Tokens -> Create Token (Custom), scoped to your account.
# Needs: Workers Scripts Edit, D1 Edit, Workers R2 Storage Edit, AI Gateway Edit, Account
# Settings Read, Secrets Store Edit, Cloudflare Tunnel Write, Connectivity Directory Admin (the
# last two let deploy.sh create the media-stack tunnel + VPC services); add Account API Tokens
# Edit (optional) so deploy.sh can auto-mint CF_AIG_TOKEN below. This is the deploy key; keep it safe.
CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=

# ---- RunPod (2b) -------------------------------------------------------------
# API key: runpod.io -> Settings -> API Keys (read/write). Runs your GPU render jobs.
RUNPOD_API_KEY=
# Endpoint id: the id of YOUR RunPod Serverless endpoint running the vivijure-backend image
# (runpod.io -> Serverless -> your endpoint). This is the "main backend" endpoint.
RUNPOD_ENDPOINT_ID=

# ---- R2 storage keys for the GPU backend (2c) --------------------------------
# dash -> R2 -> Manage R2 API Tokens -> Create API token, scoped Object Read & Write. On a FIRST
# install scope it to "all buckets": the render bucket (vivijure) does not exist until deploy.sh
# Step 2 creates it, so the bucket picker is empty on a fresh account. Narrow it to just vivijure
# after the first deploy if you like. The RunPod backend uses these over the S3 API (it is not a Worker).
R2_S3_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
R2_S3_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
# Filled in for you if left blank: endpoint is built from your account id; bucket defaults to vivijure.
R2_S3_ENDPOINT=
R2_S3_BUCKET=vivijure

# ---- AI Gateway (2d) ---------------------------------------------------------
# Gateway slug that routes the LLM/planner calls. OPTIONAL (finding F2): leave blank and the deploy
# creates an authenticated AI Gateway named "vivijure" for you (needs "AI Gateway: Edit" on your API
# token). Set this only to point at an existing gateway (dash -> AI -> AI Gateway -> your gateway).
GATEWAY_ID=

# AI Gateway auth token (a CF API token with "AI Gateway: Run"): pays the storyboard planner
# through Cloudflare Unified Billing; the plan-enhance module's Opus pass uses it too.
# OPTIONAL: leave blank and deploy.sh auto-mints a purpose-named Run-only token (needs
# "Account API Tokens: Edit" on the deploy token above). If it cannot mint, the deploy still
# completes and the final banner prints the exact dashboard steps. (Cold-deploy finding F16.)
CF_AIG_TOKEN=

# ---- Cloudflare Access (ONLY for AUTH_MODE=access; leave blank for token mode) -
# With AUTH_MODE=access the worker verifies the Access JWT in-code (fail closed) behind your edge
# Access app; deploy REFUSES to run if either value is blank. Both come from your Zero Trust setup.
# Team domain: your Zero Trust team host, like myteam.cloudflareaccess.com.
ACCESS_TEAM_DOMAIN=
# AUD: the Application Audience tag of your vivijure Access app (Zero Trust -> Access -> Applications).
ACCESS_AUD=

# ---- Optional knobs ----------------------------------------------------------
# Rate-limit bucket id for the GPU-spend limiter. Any number you pick, unique in your account.
SPEND_RATE_LIMITER_NS_ID=1001
# Cloudflare Web Analytics token for /welcome. Leave BLANK to send no analytics beacon.
UMAMI_WEBSITE_ID=

# ---- SATELLITES profile only: extra RunPod endpoints (leave blank for standard) -----
# A second RunPod endpoint id running the upscale image (finish-upscale module).
VIDEO_UPSCALE_RUNPOD_ENDPOINT_ID=
# A RunPod endpoint id running the MuseTalk lip-sync image (finish-lipsync module).
MUSETALK_RUNPOD_ENDPOINT_ID=
# A RunPod endpoint id running the audio-upscale image (speech-upscale module).
AUDIO_UPSCALE_RUNPOD_ENDPOINT_ID=

# ---- Media-stack VPC service ids: AUTOMATED, do NOT set -----------------------
# The 5 Workers VPC services (video-finish / image-prep / audio-beat-sync / audio-mix / audio-master)
# and the cloudflared tunnel are CREATED FOR YOU by deploy.sh (scripts/setup-media-vpc.py, #519); the
# service ids are rendered into the configs and the tunnel token is written to containers/tunnel.env
# (0600). There is nothing to paste here -- this replaces the old manual dashboard step.
# OPTIONAL: name the tunnel on a FIRST install (default: vivijure-media). On an UPGRADE the script
# adopts whatever tunnel your existing VPC services already point at, so this is ignored then (#531).
# VIVIJURE_TUNNEL_NAME=vivijure-media

# ---- Local-GPU door (opt-in): image-to-video on YOUR OWN local GPU box --------
# Off by default. Set to 1 ONLY after you have a local backend (vivijure-local-12gb / -16gb) door
# running; deploy.sh then deploys the local-gpu module, seeds the two secrets below into the Secrets
# Store, and binds them. See docs/DEPLOYMENT.md. (values: blank | 1)
INSTALL_LOCAL_GPU=
# Required when INSTALL_LOCAL_GPU=1 (deploy.sh fails EARLY if either is blank). Both come from your
# door box: bring the vivijure-local-12gb/-16gb container up FIRST, then copy them from its startup
# banner (the door also keeps them in its own .env):
#   LOCAL_BACKEND_URL   = the Cloudflare tunnel URL that terminates at your door box.
#                         Production fleet door (vivijure-cf): https://door-fatmike.skyphusion.org
#                         (rename CR 2026-07-21; live secret may still be door-propagandhi until apply GO).
#   LOCAL_BACKEND_TOKEN = the shared token your door checks on each render call.
LOCAL_BACKEND_URL=https://door-fatmike.skyphusion.org
LOCAL_BACKEND_TOKEN=
